OBJECTS AND CLASSES:
=====================
     Object-orientation is an approach which intends to solve real 
 world problems using programming.
     In Object Oriented programming real-world entities are 
 represented as objects
Objects:
--------
       An object can be defined as a programming representation of
real-world entity.
      An object can be created by using the blueprint or the 
 or the template returned by the programmer in the form of a class.
 Class:
 -----
  A class can be defined as a template or blue print based on 
  which object is created
 